<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-06-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-06-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="671" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d671">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 365.117/282.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Page</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Rome</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-06-08">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 8, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>318. Enrico Ajello, holder passport 51345 February this year, detained by
                            military authorities pending proof his father naturalized before his
                            birth. His brother Antonino lives 2433 First Avenue, New York. Can you
                            verify and cable Embassy?</p>
                        <closer>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy.</hi>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>